(44, 16, 37, 27, 3, 25, 26, NULL, 'Deliverance from Peril', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine deliverance in both passages. Paul asserts his Roman citizenship after being unjustly imprisoned, while Shadrach, Meshach, and Abed-nego are miraculously unharmed in the fiery furnace, showcasing God''s protection in dire circumstances.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 37, 40, 10, 16, 16, NULL, 'Wisdom in Adversity', 'Both passages emphasize the need for wisdom in challenging situations. Paul demonstrates shrewdness in asserting his rights as a Roman citizen, while Jesus advises being ''wise as serpents'' when facing danger.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 37, 44, 16, 20, 24, 'being Romans', 'Paul''s Roman Citizenship', 'Both passages emphasize Paul''s status as a Roman citizen. In Acts 16:20-24, he is identified as a Jew, yet he asserts his Roman rights in Acts 16:37, highlighting the legal implications of their treatment.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
