(44, 16, 38, 40, 14, 5, 5, NULL, 'Fear of Authority and Public Opinion', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear in both passages. In Acts, the magistrates fear the consequences of their actions upon learning Paul and Silas are Romans, while in Matthew, Herod fears the multitude''s opinion regarding John the Baptist.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 16, 38, 40, 21, 46, 46, 'feared', 'Fear of Authority and Public', 'This connection highlights the theme of fear in both passages. In Acts, the magistrates fear the consequences of their actions upon realizing the status of Paul as a Roman, while in Matthew, the authorities fear the multitude''s reaction to Jesus, whom they regard as a prophet.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
